text: Nawaf Al Habashi (; born 23 July 1998) is a Saudi Arabian footballer who plays as a midfielder for Al-Diriyah . ==Career== Al Habashi started his career at Al-Shabab and is a product of the Al-Shabab's youth system. On 26 October 2018, Al Habashi made his professional debut for Al-Shabab against Al-Qadsiah in the Pro League, replacing Waleed Al-Enezi. On 25 January 2019, Al Habashi signed a 3-year professional contract with Al-Shabab. left Al-Shabab and signed with Al-Qadsiah on loan for the 2019–20 season on July 14, 2019 . left Al-Shabab and signed with Al-Diriyah in October 16, 2020. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Saudi Arabian footballers Category:Association football midfielders Category:Al-Shabab FC (Riyadh) players Category:Al-Qadsiah FC players Category:Al-Diriyah Club players Category:Saudi Professional League players Category:Prince Mohammad bin Salman League players
